<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <% include ../partials/head %>
  <body>
    <div>
    <% include ../partials/nav %>
    <br/>

    <div class="container">

      <h1>Total Unique Nodes Found</h1>
      <p>On a daily basis the system uses 10 random "21 Computers" to ping this domain.  This is an approximation of how many 21 computers might be running out there.</p>
      <p>When the curve flattens out, it might indicate that the number of new nodes being found is slowing, and the approximate count is approaching the actual count.</p>
      <br />
      <div style="padding-left: 5%; padding-right: 5%;">
        <canvas id="myChart" ></canvas>
      </div>


      <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/Chart.js/2.1.6/Chart.min.js"></script>

      <script>
        var ctx = document.getElementById("myChart");
        Chart.defaults.global.legend.display = false;
        var myChart = new Chart(ctx, {
            type: 'line',
            data: {
                labels:  [<%= data %>],
                datasets: [{
                    data: [<%= data %>],
                    borderWidth: 1
                }]
            },
            options:
            {
                scales:
                {
                    xAxes: [{
                        display: false
                    }],
                    yAxes: [{
                        ticks: {
                            beginAtZero:true
                        }
                    }]
                }
            }
        });
        </script>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
